The paper deals with the complexity of Nash dynamics and sink equilibria in various classes of games, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses techniques from computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.DS) to solve the problems. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.SI) in some of the games studied.
